        <TextView
            android:id="@+id/textView14"
            android:layout_width="match_parent"
            android:layout_height="431dp"
            android:text="Marinate the Shrimp:

In a large bowl, combine the shrimp and Filipino brandy or gin. Let it marinate for at least 30 minutes to 1 hour in the refrigerator.
Prepare the Coating:

In a separate bowl, mix the flour, cornstarch, salt, and black pepper.
Coat the Shrimp:

Heat the cooking oil for deep-frying in a large pot or deep fryer.
Take each marinated shrimp, drain excess liquid, and coat it in the flour mixture, ensuring an even coating.
Deep Fry:

Carefully drop the coated shrimp into the hot oil. Fry in batches to avoid overcrowding.
Fry until the shrimp turn golden brown and crispy, which usually takes about 3-5 minutes.
Drain Excess Oil:

Use a slotted spoon to remove the fried shrimp from the oil. Place them on a plate lined with paper towels to drain excess oil.
Serve:

Serve the Nilasing na Hipon hot and crispy.
Optionally, serve with calamansi or lemon wedges on the side for a burst of citrus flavor."
